    10	//! warned against.
    11	//!
    12	//! Charter §0 kill_criteria_tested #1 verbatim:
    13	//!
    14	//! > If post-G-Phase batch evidence on the 9-problem set shows
    15	//! > per-problem genesis reset (balances reset, positions cleared,
    16	//! > reputation zeroed) between problems, reject — G1 ship-gate
    17	//! > violation.
    18	//!
    19	//! Six fields per charter §1 G1.2-5 ship-gate row:
    20	//!  1. balances non-flat
    21	//!  2. positions carry
    22	//!  3. reputation accumulate
    23	//!  4. PnL non-zero
    24	//!  5. autopsy not reset
    25	//!  6. model identity stable
    26	//!
    27	//! Each field is classified `Witnessed | Empty | Reset`:
    28	//!  - `Witnessed` — field shows the expected cross-task persistence
    29	//!    signature (non-flat / non-empty / monotone-add).
    30	//!  - `Empty` — clean-negative permitted per
    31	//!    `feedback_clean_negative_norm`; reported with a brief reason.
    32	//!  - `Reset` — fail-closed: field was non-empty at some task boundary
    33	//!    but reset to default at a later boundary (genesis-equivalent).
    34	//!    This is the architect §3.4 + kill-criterion #1 condition.
